metadata.name: Barbarella Dollington #4
metadata.description:
This PFP project was born from a core idea I was drawn into for many years. answering the question "what do I want my art to be about?" or "what ideas do I need to express in my art" . and my answer was "The contradictions and the contrasts". and mostly the contradiction I always found in beauty and perfection or better say in "KITSCH" 
"  kitsch is the absolute denial of shit, in both literal and figurative senses of the word; kitsch excludes everything from its purview which is essentially unacceptable in human existence." Milan Kundera writes .a kitsch can be many things , it can be a political idea, a video game , the idea of how our parents know everything or maybe a doll made specifically to look perfect. these kind of perfections shatter as we keep going on and this feeling, the feeling of a shattered kitsch is what I explore in my art and what I tried to put into this pfp project. these broken dolls come with an ironic dialogue to help you imagine their stories . This whole pfp is about the irony in shattered perfection. also they're kinda cute too ;) Enjoy!

metadata.name: Gonzion #81
metadata.description:
Gonzion is a Non-Linear Iterated Function System rendered using a method similar to Fractal Flames of Electric Sheep fame.

Technological tendrils from beyond light-aeons draw ancient crystals, transmuted fungus, sentient sigils in fossilized dimensions and alien topologies.

It's not built to run on a (2022) mobile phone and has been known to crash some, but runs fine on others.

For higher resolution renders add "#N" to the URL, default N=2.

metadata.name: Organicon, variation 00 - special edition #323
metadata.description:
Thank you!

Generative art by Frederik Vanhoutte, @wblut
One of 640 special edition generators creating an endless sequence of iterations with fixed features

Organicon, variation 00 is a slow piece, meant to build on the screen. A small counter in the lower-right corner displays the progress.

Interface: on first load the piece operates in active mode. In this mode an iteration is cleared 30s after completion and replaced by the next iteration. This mode is indicated by a flashing dot in the upper-right corner.

A first mouse click disables active mode. The current iteration will complete and remain on screen. A second mouse click clears the screen, loads the next iteration, and reenables active mode.

metadata.name: Resilience  #93
metadata.description:
Resilience is a collection of endless architectures.
In a resilient generative system composed of multiple compatible parts, real-time information exchange enables open reconfigurations and continuous discrete adjustments. Sometimes vague and fuzzy, sometimes real and tangible, they reveal different readings of architectural complexity and scale: from city plans to floor plans and details to sections and elevations.

Resilience comes in a variety of polychrome palettes, ascii glyphs, and styles. 
To enjoy it in full-screen mode, press the left mouse button in live mode, for a monochrome look press 'b'. Made with P5js.

Resilience Generative Token by @grasser_alex 2022

metadata.name: Bedlam #130
metadata.description:
Originally a study of paint brushes and texture, this project morphed. I started to find a medley of painting with the texture of handmade rugs, leveraging this medium to not just recreate the everyday, but let my imagination run. 

Enjoy each abstract piece that "Bedlam" has to offer, with 25 palettes, 5 brush styles, and an endless combination of stroke lengths and layering effects, there is much to be discovered.

It can take up to a minute for the Painting to finish, depending on your hardware.

Press 's' in Live View to save a png.

metadata.name: Refractions #275
metadata.description:
Refractions is a study of frequencies, harmonies and abstract representations of natural phenomena. 

It is an experiment of blending three colors to create integrated textural compositions.


Probabilities;

- 14 compositions with variations.

- 2 background color.

- 19 different base color palette (2 monochrome).

- 2 distinct textures with variations.

-  2 different alpha types; tangential & sinusoidal.

- Different edges.

- Several starting positions and styles (wavy or straight).


Made with p5.js

Ilgın İçözü, April 2022
@distcollective
